# Commit messages

Write commit messages as a human developer would: clear, professional, and about the code change only.

## Do not include

- Tool or editor names (Cursor, Copilot, Claude, ChatGPT, etc.)
- Phrases like "Generated by", "Co-authored-by" bots, or "AI-assisted"
- Session or agent references

## Do include

- What changed and why, in plain language
- Conventional prefix when it fits the repo (`fix:`, `fix(ci):`, `feat:`, `docs:`)
- One focused subject line; optional short body for non-obvious context

## Examples

```
# Good
fix(ci): add /home ACL script for self-hosted runner on cPanel

# Bad
fix(ci): Cursor added ACL script for runner
Add runner fix (AI-generated)
Co-authored-by: Cursor <noreply@cursor.com>
```
